body:
I was pleased to see that there will be a tank rework in the future with a focus on tanks that like to engage the enemy team.  Leona was the first tank support that I got and I loved playing her as she felt fun, engaging and powerful with all the CC she has.  To me she is the definition of what you guys are aiming to rework.  The minor changes she received last were nice in that it brought more CC to her kit but she still really struggles to find a place in lane this season.  I have a few questions about her and a couple suggestions.

First, I would like to ask &quot;Is she in the tank rework?&quot; 
Second, &quot;If so, will she get a big update or just minor changes?&quot;  
Third, &quot;What do you think she needs to be a competitive pick again?&quot;
Fourth, &quot;What do you feel is core to her identity?&quot;

I&#039;m sure a lot of people have great ideas about Leona and her direction but I have always wanted to feel like this great protector with her.  When I do get a game I feel she can play in I always feel so great about when I am able to protect my allies with my CC.  It feels great to engage on the enemy too but I always enjoy the feeling of protecting my allies more.  I&#039;ve felt her kit to her theme is a bit....confusing.  She has all this CC but her passive just adds some damage.  She is encouraged to always engage but rarely to protect.  I wish her passive was something more focused on Protecting rather then damaging, I feel that she never really makes use of her shield because of this.  If she is the shield bearing protector of the sun shouldn&#039;t that be a bigger part of her identity?
